  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD061454",
      "title": "MDM2 influenced chromatin-associated phospho-peptides in T47D cells",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Employing a stable isotope labeling in cell culture analysis in T47D breast cancer cells (expressing mtp53 L194F), we uncovered several chromatin-associated DNA replication and repair factors as MDM2-regulated (by MDM2 inducible knock-down) phosphoproteins, including 53BP1",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Phosphoproteome SILAC Screen of Chromatin Targets: We carried out Stable Isotope Labeling of Cell Culture SILAC using T47D cells with or without MDM2 expression. We isolated phospho-peptides before mass spectrometry by their strong affinity for metal ions on strong cation exchange (SCX) chromatography, which separates peptides by solution charge followed by immobilized metal affinity chromatography (IMAC) to enrich the phospho-peptides [1, 2]. This was followed by two-dimensional (2D) nano-liquid chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry (LC/MS). We first fractionated the T47D.shmdm2 cell extract (with and without MDM2 knockdown) into chromatin, nuclear soluble and cytoplasmic fractions.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "We then analyzed the chromatin-associated phospho-peptides for the influence of MDM2 knockdown. This method identified that numerous phospho-peptides were involved in an MDM2 signal transduction cascade that influenced the chromatin. A total of N=1381 phospho-peptides were identified from SILAC experiments. The fold change of intensities (examined as the heavy to light ratio) of these peptides between the samples with and without MDM2 knockdown (y-axis) were plotted against their average intensities (x-axis, log2 scale). Our customized interactive plot showing all peptides is available on http://diverge.hunter.cuny.edu/~weigang/clickme-khalikuz/temp-Points.html. Four groups of peptides were found which included peptides in lower abundance that were absent when MDM2 was knocked down (lower cloud), and those present in high abundance that were either reduced, or not changed with MDM2 knockdown (cloud close to the fold change=0 line, with below 0 showing reduction). We also detected peptides in low and high abundance that were present only after MDM2 knockdown.",
      "projectTags": [],
      "keywords": [
        "Chromatin-associated",
        "Phospho-peptides",
        "Mdm2",
        "53bp1"
      ],
